      <hedline>
        <hl1>CLOCKWISE, EVERYWHERE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Glenn Weinstein letter on Matt Gross's January 7 Frugal Traveler column on Punta del Este, Uruguay</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: ''Punta del Este, Uruguay; Feeling at Home Among the Elite'' by Matt Gross (Frugal Traveler, Jan. 7), repeats an age-old urban legend: that water spins down a drain counterclockwise in the southern hemisphere: ''I could hear the money running merrily down the drain -- counterclockwise, of course: this was the Southern Hemisphere.''</p>
        <p>There's just one problem: it ain't so.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: ''Punta del Este, Uruguay; Feeling at Home Among the Elite'' by Matt Gross (Frugal Traveler, Jan. 7), repeats an age-old urban legend: that water spins down a drain counterclockwise in the southern hemisphere: ''I could hear the money running merrily down the drain -- counterclockwise, of course: this was the Southern Hemisphere.''</p>
        <p>There's just one problem: it ain't so.</p>
        <p>For a full debunking of this alleged effect, please see snopes.com/science/coriolis.asp.</p>
        <p>Glenn Weinstein  Marietta, Ga.</p>
      </block>
